>>46350319
I believe you'd need to provide attribution and license any derived assets under CC-BY-SA if you normalise, loop, remix, or otherwise modify the song. I don't think the entire game is a derivative work or an adaptation, but the specific assets definitely would be. Also, CC has specific rules for music videos that probably mean your promotional material needs to be CC-BY-SA if it features those songs.

Rationale on not needing to release the whole thing as CC-BY-SA: https://opensource.stackexchange.com/questions/173/what-do-i-need-to-share-if-i-include-cc-by-sa-artwork-in-my-software. There's not a clear path from one song to any of your 3D models, or to the game's code. If you avoid doing anything really dumb that would make the entire game derivative I think it's fine.
